					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>330 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>398</height>
										<width>275</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>280</height>
										<width>220</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>330 folios (+ 3 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 1 older and 4 modern paper flyleaves at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>15 quires of 8 leaves each (folios 1-120), signed at the end with Hebrew letters (numbering continues from the previous volume, Add. 17049).</p>
									<p>25 quires of 8 leaves each (folios 126-325), signed at the end with Hebrew letters.</p>
									<p>Folio 326 is a separate leaf and folio 327 is a paper flyleaf attached to the manuscript in 1610 or later.</p>
									<p>Folios 328-330 belonged earlier to a different manuscript.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>The lower section of folio 323 has been cut  with loss of text.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="35" writtenLines="34">
									<p>Varying layout. Visible page by page pricking and plummet (brown) ruling, also for the margins.</p>
									<p>Repeated words at the beginning of the columns.</p>
									<p>Commentary in a small semi-cursive script provided around the main text.</p>
									<p>Last line of writing written within the ruling.</p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable.</p>
									<p>Occasional additional notes.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi square and Ashkenazi semi-cursive script of the 14th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Shemayah</name>: his name marked off on folio 19r and 105r, and marked off in acrostic on folio 41v and 236v.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 327: an Italian document (paper), dated Lugo, Febr. 16, <date calendar="Gregorian">1610</date>, by which permission was given to Salvator Salamon Ravena to transfer this manuscript to Modena. There are several names appearing in the document: L. Franguelli, inquisitore et riveditore; Fr. Agostino da Lugo, vicario di santo offizo di Lugo; Fr. Julius de Lugo, loco vicarii; Fr. Paulus, inquisitor Bonon.; Fr. Michael Angelus, inquisitor Mutinensis; Fr. Stephanus di Meldola, notarius inquisitorius Mutinensis (?).</p>
							<p>Folios 328-330: fragments of Pisḳe ha-Rosh; each page is divided into 3 columns with 48 lines to a column. Ashkenazi square script of porbably the 14th century.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Mosheh Shapira</name>: inscribed (folio 126r), perhaps the same as Mosheh ben Yosef mentioned in the colophon on page 210v, volume 1, Add. 17049.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Camillo Jaghel</name>: inscribed with his name, <date calendar="Gregorian">1613 </date>(folio 326v); see <ref target="Popper_1969"/>, appendix § 50-56.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Renatus a Mutina</name>: inscribed with his name, <date calendar="Gregorian">1621</date> (folio 326v).</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Gir[olamo] de Durallano</name> [de Predi?]: censor's signature and note <date calendar="Gregorian">1640</date> (folio 326v) , on him see <ref target="Popper_1969"/>, appendix § 89.</p>
						</additions>
